Law enforcement officers say the use of the modern technologies has made it harder to determine if a threat is real . 
  National School Safety and Security Services reviewed more than 800 school threats in the first half of 2014-15 . 
  Researchers found that about one-third of cases involved violent remarks sent anonymously via text message, social media, email or other online means . 
  Authorities say the majority of the time threats turn out to be hoaxes . 
 